message.content: This question requires some basic knowledge about erosion and geological processes. Over time, when a boulder is exposed to various elements such as heat from the sun, crashing waves, and storms, it will undergo weathering and erosion. This means that the boulder will break down, get worn away, and gradually disintegrate into smaller pieces. These smaller pieces will then become part of the surrounding soil, resulting in the area where the boulder stood becoming earth. Options (B), (C), and (D) are not related to geological processes and are therefore incorrect.
